Rating: 4
This is great, by itself or served over ice cream, shortbread or angel food cake. It is very easy. The last time I made it, I used a cabernet. Delicious and so so easy.

Rating: 4
I used fresh plums and raspberries from our garden for this recipe and it was delicious. It's a great light dessert, perfect after a big meal. It is important to allow the compote to chill overnight. I tried it the night I made it and it tasted too "winey". However, the night I served it, the juices had blended and it tasted great. All the guests raved.

Rating: 3
Simple, elegant, and scrumptious! A perfect summer dessert!